{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0001","metadata":{},"source":["# FraudScope — 02 MLOps : Tracking, Registry & Serving\n","## Phase 2 · Dataset IEEE-CIS · MLflow · XGBoost · SHAP\n","\n","**Objectifs de ce notebook** :\n","1. Installer et configurer MLflow comme serveur de tracking\n","2. Comparer 5 stratégies de resampling sur XGBoost avec tracking complet des runs\n","3. Identifier le meilleur modèle et l'enregistrer dans le MLflow Model Registry\n","4. Servir le modèle via une API REST\n","5. Expliquer les prédictions avec SHAP et logger les artefacts\n","\n","**Prérequis** : avoir complété `01_exploration.ipynb` et suivi `docs/phase2_mlflow_guide.md`.\n","\n","> ⚠️ Le serveur MLflow doit être lancé **avant** d'exécuter ce notebook :\n","> ```\n","> mlflow server --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8080 --backend-store-uri ./mlruns --default-artifact-root ./mlruns\n","> ```"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0002","metadata":{},"source":["## 0. Imports et configuration"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0003","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["import warnings\n","warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n","\n","from pathlib import Path\n","import os\n","import time\n","\n","import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns\n","\n","from dotenv import load_dotenv\n","import mlflow\n","import mlflow.xgboost\n","from mlflow.tracking import MlflowClient\n","\n","from sklearn.model_selection import TimeSeriesSplit\n","from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n","from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n","from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\n","from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OrdinalEncoder\n","from sklearn.metrics import (\n","    recall_score, f1_score, average_precision_score,\n","    precision_recall_curve\n",")\n","\n","import xgboost as xgb\n","from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE\n","from imblearn.combine import SMOTEENN\n","\n","import shap\n","\n","# ── Configuration ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid')\n","pd.set_option('display.max_columns', 50)\n","pd.set_option('display.float_format', '{:.4f}'.format)\n","\n","FIGURES_DIR   = Path('figures')\n","ARTIFACTS_DIR = Path('artifacts')\n","FIGURES_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n","ARTIFACTS_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n","\n","RANDOM_STATE = 42\n","TARGET       = 'isFraud'\n","\n","# ── MLflow setup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# Charger les variables d'environnement depuis .env\n","load_dotenv()\n","\n","TRACKING_URI     = os.getenv('MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI', 'http://127.0.0.1:8080')\n","EXPERIMENT_NAME  = os.getenv('MLFLOW_EXPERIMENT_NAME', 'fraud-detection-paytrack')\n","MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME = 'FraudScopeXGB'\n","\n","# Connexion au serveur MLflow\n","mlflow.set_tracking_uri(TRACKING_URI)\n","mlflow.set_experiment(EXPERIMENT_NAME)\n","\n","print(f'MLflow tracking URI : {TRACKING_URI}')\n","print(f'Expérience          : {EXPERIMENT_NAME}')\n","print(f'MLflow version      : {mlflow.__version__}')\n","print('Imports OK')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0004","metadata":{},"source":["## 1. Chargement et préparation des données\n","\n","On réutilise les mêmes données que la Phase 1.\n","Les features de vélocité sont recalculées ici pour être disponibles dans ce notebook."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0005","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["DATA_DIR = Path('data')\n","\n","assert (DATA_DIR / 'train_transaction.csv').exists(), 'Données manquantes → voir data/get_dataset.md'\n","\n","print('Chargement des données...')\n","train_tx = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / 'train_transaction.csv')\n","train_id = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / 'train_identity.csv')\n","\n","df = train_tx.merge(train_id, on='TransactionID', how='left')\n","df = df.sort_values('TransactionDT').reset_index(drop=True)\n","print(f'Dataset : {df.shape[0]:,} transactions, {df.shape[1]} colonnes')\n","\n","# Réduction mémoire (downcast int64 → int32/16/8, float64 → float32)\n","def reduce_mem_usage(df):\n","    for col in df.select_dtypes(include=['int64', 'float64']).columns:\n","        col_min, col_max = df[col].min(), df[col].max()\n","        if str(df[col].dtype).startswith('int'):\n","            if   col_min >= np.iinfo(np.int8).min  and col_max <= np.iinfo(np.int8).max:\n","                df[col] = df[col].astype(np.int8)\n","            elif col_min >= np.iinfo(np.int16).min and col_max <= np.iinfo(np.int16).max:\n","                df[col] = df[col].astype(np.int16)\n","            else:\n","                df[col] = df[col].astype(np.int32)\n","        else:\n","            if col_min >= np.finfo(np.float32).min and col_max <= np.finfo(np.float32).max:\n","                df[col] = df[col].astype(np.float32)\n","    return df\n","\n","df = reduce_mem_usage(df)\n","print('Downcast mémoire appliqué.')"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0006","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# ── Features temporelles (reprises de la Phase 1) ───────────────────────────\n","df['hour']  = (df['TransactionDT'] // 3600) % 24\n","df['day']   =  df['TransactionDT'] // (3600 * 24)\n","\n","# Proxy client (combinaison carte + adresse)\n","proxy_cols = [c for c in ['card1','card2','card3','card4','card5','card6','addr1','addr2'] if c in df.columns]\n","df['customer_proxy'] = df[proxy_cols].astype(str).fillna('NA').agg('_'.join, axis=1)\n","df['tx_time_sec']    = df['TransactionDT'].astype(float)\n","\n","# ── Features de vélocité simplifiées (count rolling par client) ─────────────\n","# Note : pour la Phase 2, on utilise des proxies plus rapides à calculer\n","# (rank-based plutôt que rolling window python pur) pour éviter les timeouts\n","df['tx_rank_in_customer'] = df.groupby('customer_proxy').cumcount()\n","\n","# Ratio montant (montant courant / médiane des montants du client)\n","df['amount_ratio'] = df['TransactionAmt'] / (\n","    df.groupby('customer_proxy')['TransactionAmt']\n","    .transform('median')\n","    .clip(lower=0.01)\n",")\n","df['amount_ratio'] = df['amount_ratio'].replace([np.inf, -np.inf], 1.0).fillna(1.0)\n","\n","print('Features temporelles et vélocité créées.')\n","print(df[['hour', 'day', 'tx_rank_in_customer', 'amount_ratio', TARGET]].describe())"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0007","metadata":{},"source":["## 2. Préparation du pipeline de prétraitement"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0008","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# ── Sélection des features ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","exclude = {'TransactionID', TARGET, 'customer_proxy', 'tx_time_sec'}\n","high_missing = df.columns[df.isna().mean() > 0.95].tolist()\n","all_features = [c for c in df.columns if c not in exclude and c not in high_missing]\n","\n","X = df[all_features]\n","y = df[TARGET]\n","\n","num_features = X.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\n","cat_features = X.select_dtypes(exclude=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\n","\n","print(f'Features numériques   : {len(num_features)}')\n","print(f'Features catégorielles : {len(cat_features)}')\n","print(f'Total                 : {len(all_features)}')\n","\n","# ── Preprocessor sklearn ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# XGBoost gère nativement les NaN → pas de StandardScaler nécessaire\n","# On utilise un OrdinalEncoder pour les catégorielles (XGBoost accepte les entiers)\n","\n","num_transformer = SimpleImputer(strategy='median')\n","\n","cat_transformer = Pipeline([\n","    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent')),\n","    ('encoder', OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1))\n","])\n","\n","preprocessor = ColumnTransformer([\n","    ('num', num_transformer, num_features),\n","    ('cat', cat_transformer, cat_features),\n","], remainder='drop')\n","\n","# Split temporel final : 80% train, 20% test\n","split_idx = int(len(df) * 0.8)\n","X_train_raw, X_test_raw = X.iloc[:split_idx], X.iloc[split_idx:]\n","y_train,     y_test     = y.iloc[:split_idx], y.iloc[split_idx:]\n","\n","# Prétraitement\n","X_train = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train_raw)\n","X_test  = preprocessor.transform(X_test_raw)\n","\n","print(f'Train : {X_train.shape}  |  Test : {X_test.shape}')\n","print(f'Ratio fraude train : {y_train.mean():.4f}  |  test : {y_test.mean():.4f}')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0009","metadata":{},"source":["## 3. Comparaison des stratégies de resampling avec MLflow\n","\n","On compare 5 stratégies pour gérer le déséquilibre de classes :\n","\n","| # | Stratégie | Principe |\n","|---|-----------|----------|\n","| 1 | **Baseline** | Aucun resampling — XGBoost sur données brutes |\n","| 2 | **Class weighting** | `scale_pos_weight` = nb_négatifs / nb_positifs |\n","| 3 | **Undersampling** | Réduction aléatoire de la classe majoritaire |\n","| 4 | **SMOTE** | Génération synthétique d'exemples frauduleux |\n","| 5 | **SMOTE+ENN** | SMOTE + nettoyage des frontières de décision |\n","\n","**Chaque stratégie génère un run MLflow indépendant**, loggant paramètres, métriques et artefacts."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0010","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# ── Paramètres XGBoost communs à toutes les stratégies ──────────────────────\n","# Ces paramètres seront loggués dans chaque run MLflow (mlflow.log_params)\n","XGB_BASE_PARAMS = {\n","    'n_estimators':     300,\n","    'max_depth':        6,\n","    'learning_rate':    0.05,\n","    'subsample':        0.8,\n","    'colsample_bytree': 0.8,\n","    'eval_metric':      'aucpr',       # Optimiser AUPRC directement\n","    'early_stopping_rounds': 20,       # Arrêt si pas d'amélioration sur 20 rounds\n","    'random_state':     RANDOM_STATE,\n","    'n_jobs':           -1\n","}\n","\n","# Ratio de déséquilibre (pour scale_pos_weight)\n","neg_count = (y_train == 0).sum()\n","pos_count = (y_train == 1).sum()\n","imbalance_ratio = neg_count / pos_count\n","print(f'Ratio déséquilibre : {imbalance_ratio:.1f}  ({neg_count:,} légitimes / {pos_count:,} fraudes)')"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0011","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["def run_strategy(strategy_name, X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val, extra_params=None):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Entraîne un XGBoost et logue tout dans MLflow.\n","    \n","    Parameters\n","    ----------\n","    strategy_name : str     Nom de la stratégie (ex: 'smote')\n","    X_tr, y_tr    : arrays  Données d'entraînement (après resampling éventuel)\n","    X_val, y_val  : arrays  Données de validation (jamais resamplees)\n","    extra_params  : dict    Paramètres XGBoost supplémentaires (ex: scale_pos_weight)\n","    \n","    Returns\n","    -------\n","    dict : métriques du run\n","    \"\"\"\n","    params = {**XGB_BASE_PARAMS, **(extra_params or {})}\n","\n","    with mlflow.start_run(run_name=f'xgb-{strategy_name}') as run:\n","\n","        # Tags : métadonnées décrivant ce run\n","        mlflow.set_tags({\n","            'dataset':  'IEEE-CIS',\n","            'model':    'XGBoost',\n","            'strategy': strategy_name,\n","            'phase':    '2'\n","        })\n","\n","        # Logger les hyperparamètres\n","        mlflow.log_params(params)\n","        mlflow.log_param('train_size',  len(y_tr))\n","        mlflow.log_param('fraud_rate_train', float(y_tr.mean()))\n","\n","        # Entraînement avec early stopping\n","        t0 = time.time()\n","        model = xgb.XGBClassifier(**params)\n","        model.fit(\n","            X_tr, y_tr,\n","            eval_set=[(X_val, y_val)],\n","            verbose=False\n","        )\n","        fit_time = time.time() - t0\n","\n","        # Métriques d'évaluation\n","        y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\n","        y_pred  = (y_proba >= 0.5).astype(int)\n","\n","        auprc  = average_precision_score(y_val, y_proba)\n","        recall = recall_score(y_val, y_pred)\n","        f1     = f1_score(y_val, y_pred)\n","\n","        metrics = {\n","            'AUPRC':        auprc,\n","            'recall_fraud': recall,\n","            'f1':           f1,\n","            'fit_time_sec': fit_time\n","        }\n","        mlflow.log_metrics(metrics)\n","\n","        # Artefact : courbe Precision-Recall\n","        precision_vals, recall_vals, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_val, y_proba)\n","        fig_pr, ax_pr = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 5))\n","        ax_pr.plot(recall_vals, precision_vals, lw=2, color='steelblue')\n","        ax_pr.fill_between(recall_vals, precision_vals, alpha=0.1, color='steelblue')\n","        ax_pr.set_xlabel('Recall')\n","        ax_pr.set_ylabel('Precision')\n","        ax_pr.set_title(f'Courbe PR — {strategy_name} (AUPRC={auprc:.4f})')\n","        ax_pr.set_xlim(0, 1); ax_pr.set_ylim(0, 1)\n","        mlflow.log_figure(fig_pr, 'pr_curve.png')\n","        plt.close(fig_pr)\n","\n","        # Sauvegarder le modèle au format MLflow\n","        # (inclut la signature, les dépendances pip, et le modèle sérialisé)\n","        mlflow.xgboost.log_model(model, artifact_path='model')\n","\n","        print(f'  [{strategy_name:20s}] AUPRC={auprc:.4f}  Recall={recall:.4f}  F1={f1:.4f}  ({fit_time:.1f}s)')\n","        return {**metrics, 'run_id': run.info.run_id, 'strategy': strategy_name}\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0012","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["all_results = []\n","\n","print('=== Entraînement des 5 stratégies — runs MLflow loggués ===\\n')\n","\n","# ─── Stratégie 1 : Baseline ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# Aucun resampling. XGBoost verra ~96.5% de classe 0 et ~3.5% de classe 1.\n","# Attendu : bon AUPRC mais recall faible.\n","all_results.append(run_strategy('baseline', X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test))\n","\n","# ─── Stratégie 2 : Class weighting ────────────────────────────────────────\n","# scale_pos_weight indique à XGBoost de pénaliser davantage les faux négatifs.\n","# Valeur standard = nb_négatifs / nb_positifs (le ratio de déséquilibre).\n","all_results.append(run_strategy(\n","    'class_weighting', X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test,\n","    extra_params={'scale_pos_weight': imbalance_ratio}\n","))\n","\n","# ─── Stratégie 3 : Undersampling ──────────────────────────────────────────\n","# On garde toutes les fraudes et on sous-échantillonne les légitimes.\n","# Ratio 1:10 (10 légitimes pour 1 fraude) — compromis entre biais et vitesse.\n","from imblearn.under_sampling import RandomUnderSampler\n","rus = RandomUnderSampler(sampling_strategy=0.1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\n","X_under, y_under = rus.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)\n","all_results.append(run_strategy('undersampling', X_under, y_under, X_test, y_test))\n","\n","# ─── Stratégie 4 : SMOTE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# Synthetic Minority Over-sampling Technique : génère des exemples synthétiques\n","# de fraude par interpolation entre exemples voisins.\n","# Ratio 0.2 = on monte jusqu'à 20% de fraudes dans le train set.\n","smote = SMOTE(sampling_strategy=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, n_jobs=-1)\n","X_smote, y_smote = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)\n","print(f'  SMOTE : {y_smote.sum():,} fraudes synthétiques + réelles dans le train')\n","all_results.append(run_strategy('smote', X_smote, y_smote, X_test, y_test))\n","\n","# ─── Stratégie 5 : SMOTE+ENN ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# SMOTE + Edited Nearest Neighbours : après le suréchantillonnage SMOTE,\n","# on supprime les exemples mal classés par leurs voisins (nettoyage des frontières).\n","# Plus lent mais souvent meilleur recall.\n","smoteenn = SMOTEENN(sampling_strategy=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, n_jobs=-1)\n","X_smoteenn, y_smoteenn = smoteenn.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)\n","all_results.append(run_strategy('smote_enn', X_smoteenn, y_smoteenn, X_test, y_test))\n","\n","# ── Tableau récapitulatif ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","results_df = pd.DataFrame(all_results).set_index('strategy')\n","print('\\n=== Résultats comparatifs ===')\n","print(results_df[['AUPRC', 'recall_fraud', 'f1', 'fit_time_sec']].to_string())"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0013","metadata":{},"source":["## 4. Sélection du meilleur modèle\n","\n","On interroge MLflow pour récupérer le run avec le meilleur AUPRC.\n","C'est **MLflow qui fait autorité** : pas de variable Python en dur."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0014","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# Récupérer tous les runs de l'expérience, triés par AUPRC décroissant\n","df_runs = mlflow.search_runs(\n","    experiment_names=[EXPERIMENT_NAME],\n","    order_by=['metrics.AUPRC DESC']\n",")\n","\n","print('=== Runs de l\'expérience (triés par AUPRC décroissant) ===')\n","print(df_runs[['tags.mlflow.runName', 'metrics.AUPRC', 'metrics.recall_fraud', 'metrics.f1', 'run_id']].to_string())\n","\n","best_run = df_runs.iloc[0]\n","best_run_id = best_run['run_id']\n","best_auprc  = best_run['metrics.AUPRC']\n","best_name   = best_run['tags.mlflow.runName']\n","\n","print(f'\\n✅ Meilleur run : {best_name}')\n","print(f'   AUPRC       : {best_auprc:.4f}')\n","print(f'   Run ID      : {best_run_id}')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0015","metadata":{},"source":["## 5. Enregistrement dans le Model Registry\n","\n","Le Model Registry est la \"bibliothèque officielle\" des modèles du projet.\n","Seuls les modèles enregistrés ici peuvent être déployés en production."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0016","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# URI du modèle dans le run MLflow\n","model_uri = f'runs:/{best_run_id}/model'\n","\n","# Enregistrement dans le Registry\n","# Si le modèle existe déjà, MLflow crée une nouvelle version automatiquement.\n","print(f'Enregistrement du modèle dans le Registry sous le nom \'{MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME}\'...')\n","registered_model = mlflow.register_model(model_uri=model_uri, name=MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME)\n","\n","model_version = registered_model.version\n","print(f'✅ Modèle enregistré : {MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME} v{model_version}')\n","\n","# Ajouter une description pour la traçabilité\n","client = MlflowClient()\n","client.update_model_version(\n","    name=MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME,\n","    version=model_version,\n","    description=f'XGBoost entraîné sur IEEE-CIS. Stratégie : {best_name}. AUPRC : {best_auprc:.4f}'\n",")"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0017","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# ── Transition Staging → Production ─────────────────────────────────────────\n","# Bonne pratique : passer par Staging avant Production\n","# (en entreprise, Staging déclenche les tests d'intégration automatiques)\n","\n","print(f'Transition {MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME} v{model_version} : None → Staging')\n","client.transition_model_version_stage(\n","    name=MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME,\n","    version=model_version,\n","    stage='Staging'\n",")\n","\n","# Validation gate : on vérifie que le modèle en Staging atteint le seuil minimum\n","AUPRC_THRESHOLD = 0.50  # Seuil minimal pour aller en Production\n","\n","if best_auprc >= AUPRC_THRESHOLD:\n","    print(f'✅ AUPRC={best_auprc:.4f} ≥ seuil={AUPRC_THRESHOLD} → Promotion en Production')\n","    client.transition_model_version_stage(\n","        name=MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME,\n","        version=model_version,\n","        stage='Production'\n","    )\n","else:\n","    print(f'❌ AUPRC={best_auprc:.4f} < seuil={AUPRC_THRESHOLD} → Reste en Staging. Investiguer.')\n","\n","print(f'\\nVotre modèle est visible dans l\'UI MLflow → onglet \"Models\" : http://127.0.0.1:8080')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0018","metadata":{},"source":["## 6. Serving : tester l'API REST\n","\n","Avant d'exécuter cette section, lance le serveur de prédiction dans un nouveau terminal :\n","\n","```bash\n","mlflow models serve \\\n","  --model-uri models:/FraudScopeXGB/Production \\\n","  --host 127.0.0.1 \\\n","  --port 5001 \\\n","  --no-conda\n","```"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0019","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["import requests, json\n","\n","SERVING_URL = 'http://127.0.0.1:5001/invocations'\n","\n","# Prendre 3 transactions du test set pour illustrer\n","sample_indices = [0, 1, 2]\n","\n","# Convertir en format dict colonne pour l'API MLflow\n","if hasattr(X_test, 'toarray'):\n","    X_sample = X_test[sample_indices].toarray()\n","else:\n","    X_sample = X_test[sample_indices]\n","\n","payload = {\n","    'dataframe_split': {\n","        'columns': [str(i) for i in range(X_sample.shape[1])],\n","        'data': X_sample.tolist()\n","    }\n","}\n","\n","try:\n","    response = requests.post(\n","        SERVING_URL,\n","        headers={'Content-Type': 'application/json'},\n","        data=json.dumps(payload),\n","        timeout=5\n","    )\n","    response.raise_for_status()\n","    predictions = response.json()['predictions']\n","    print('Prédictions API REST (probabilité de fraude) :')\n","    for i, (proba, true_label) in enumerate(zip(predictions, y_test.iloc[sample_indices].values)):\n","        flag = '🚨' if proba > 0.5 else '✅'\n","        print(f'  Transaction {i+1} : P(fraude)={proba:.4f}  (vraie étiquette={true_label})  {flag}')\n","except requests.exceptions.ConnectionError:\n","    print('⚠️  Serveur de prédiction non démarré.')\n","    print('   Lance : mlflow models serve --model-uri models:/FraudScopeXGB/Production --host 127.0.0.1 --port 5001 --no-conda')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0020","metadata":{},"source":["## 7. Explainabilité SHAP\n","\n","SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations) permet de comprendre **pourquoi** le modèle a prédit fraude ou légitif pour une transaction donnée.\n","\n","- **Beeswarm global** : quelles features influencent le plus le modèle sur l'ensemble du test set\n","- **Force plot local** : pourquoi le modèle a dit \"fraude\" sur une transaction précise"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0021","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# Charger le meilleur modèle depuis le Registry\n","print('Chargement du modèle depuis MLflow Registry...')\n","loaded_model = mlflow.xgboost.load_model(f'models:/{MODEL_REGISTRY_NAME}/Production')\n","\n","# SHAP sur un sous-ensemble (500 transactions pour la rapidité)\n","N_SHAP = 500\n","if hasattr(X_test, 'toarray'):\n","    X_shap = X_test[:N_SHAP].toarray()\n","else:\n","    X_shap = X_test[:N_SHAP]\n","\n","print(f'Calcul des valeurs SHAP sur {N_SHAP} transactions...')\n","explainer    = shap.TreeExplainer(loaded_model)\n","shap_values  = explainer.shap_values(X_shap)\n","\n","# Récupérer les noms de features après le ColumnTransformer\n","cat_feature_names = preprocessor.named_transformers_['cat']['encoder'].get_feature_names_out(cat_features).tolist()\n","feature_names = num_features + cat_feature_names\n","\n","print('Valeurs SHAP calculées.')"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0022","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# ── Beeswarm global ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","fig_beeswarm, ax_beeswarm = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\n","shap.summary_plot(\n","    shap_values,\n","    features=X_shap,\n","    feature_names=feature_names,\n","    max_display=20,\n","    plot_type='dot',\n","    show=False\n",")\n","plt.title('SHAP Beeswarm — Top 20 features influentes (FraudScopeXGB)')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","\n","# Logger l'artefact dans le run MLflow du meilleur modèle\n","with mlflow.start_run(run_id=best_run_id):\n","    mlflow.log_figure(plt.gcf(), 'shap_beeswarm.png')\n","\n","plt.savefig(FIGURES_DIR / 'shap_beeswarm_phase2.png', dpi=150)\n","plt.show()\n","print('Beeswarm loggué dans MLflow et sauvegardé dans figures/')"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"id":"b2c3d4e5-0023","metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# ── Analyse locale : une vraie fraude détectée ──────────────────────────────\n","# On cherche le premier vrai positif (fraude réelle, prédite fraude)\n","y_test_vals  = y_test.values[:N_SHAP]\n","y_proba_shap = loaded_model.predict_proba(X_shap)[:, 1]\n","\n","tp_indices = np.where((y_test_vals == 1) & (y_proba_shap >= 0.5))[0]\n","fp_indices = np.where((y_test_vals == 0) & (y_proba_shap >= 0.5))[0]\n","\n","if len(tp_indices) > 0:\n","    idx_tp = tp_indices[0]\n","    print(f'Vrai positif analysé (index {idx_tp}) : P(fraude)={y_proba_shap[idx_tp]:.4f}')\n","    shap.force_plot(\n","        explainer.expected_value,\n","        shap_values[idx_tp],\n","        features=X_shap[idx_tp],\n","        feature_names=feature_names,\n","        matplotlib=True, show=False\n","    )\n","    plt.title(f'SHAP Force Plot — Vrai Positif (index {idx_tp})')\n","    plt.tight_layout()\n","    plt.savefig(FIGURES_DIR / 'shap_force_vrai_positif.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n","    plt.show()\n","else:\n","    print('Pas de vrai positif dans les 500 premières transactions de test. Augmenter N_SHAP.')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"b2c3d4e5-0024","metadata":{},"source":["## 8. Bilan Phase 2\n","\n","| Élément | Statut |\n","|---------|--------|\n","| Serveur MLflow local | ✅ |\n","| 5 stratégies XGBoost loggées | ✅ |\n","| Courbes PR artefacts MLflow | ✅ |\n","| Meilleur modèle dans Registry | ✅ |\n","| Validation gate AUPRC | ✅ |\n","| Serving REST `/invocations` | ✅ |\n","| SHAP beeswarm global | ✅ |\n","| SHAP force plot local | ✅ |\n","\n","**Prochaine étape** : Phase 3 — Features graphe (NetworkX) + GNN sur dataset Elliptic (GCN/GAT via PyTorch Geometric).","\n","Le notebook `03_graphnn.ipynb` reprendra l'entraînement dans Jupyter, sur un dataset différent (graphe de transactions Bitcoin)."]}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.11.0"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}